_:N06bb2dd373574a77b4d959f633d14e77 <http://schema.org/description> "<p>Shirley has most recently been the chief people officer at Scottish Water, where she was accountable for all people practices, engagement and internal communications, people change, workplaces, enterprise-wide transformation and digital, and hybrid working.</p>\n\n<p>Preceding this she was the people and organisational development director at Heriot Watt University and the UK HR and corporate services director at Royal and Sun Alliance.</p>\n\n<p>The majority of her earlier career was spent at Aviva Plc in roles such as UK organisational development director and HR director for general insurance.</p>\n\n<p>Additionally, she was the President of Water Aid Scotland and was a founding board member of Scotland’s Senior HR Leadership Group.</p>\n\n<p>She is a former non-executive director of Scotland’s Fair Work Convention and BT Scotland and is a past Lay Member of Court at Dundee University, where she was chair of the People and Organisational Development Committee and a member of the RemCo.</p>\n\n<p>Furthermore she has also held chair accountability for both Scottish Water Horizons - a standalone commercial renewables business, and Scottish Water International - a commercial business offering services and expertise to governments and water companies globally.</p>\n\n<p>In her previous roles she has significant remuneration committee experience, in both executive and non-executive capacities.</p>\n\n<p>She was appointed as a Sellafield Ltd non-executive director in May 2024.</p>\n" .
<https://www.gov.uk/> <http://schema.org/name> "Home" .
